  "market_context": "Uptrend on EURUSD 5-min chart; price broke structure to the upside with no inefficiency (no FVG/imbalance) in the latest impulse move. Left-side analysis revealed prior inefficiency below the most recent swing low and a valid order block zone.",
  "key_observation": "Price is likely to sweep below the swing low to grab liquidity (SSL), then reverse upward into the nearby order block demand area for a high-probability long entry.",
  "analysis_steps": [
    "Step 1: The analyst examined the left side of the market structure to assess trade quality, noting the absence of inefficiency in the latest bullish impulse move.",
    "Step 2: The analyst identified prior inefficiency just below the most recent swing low and a valid order block (OB) zone positioned beneath the current price action.",
    "Step 3: Based on this setup, the analyst anticipated a liquidity sweep below the swing low (SSL grab), followed by a reversal into the OB demand area for a long entry.",
    "Step 4: The trade plan specified placing a buy order a spread above the OB zone, stop-loss below the swing low, and targeting the next resistance level ahead."
  ],
  "outcome": null,
  "lessons": "In an uptrend with no inefficiency in the latest impulse, price often sweeps liquidity below the swing low before reversing into a nearby order block—this pattern offers high-probability entries when confirmed by left-side structure analysis.",
